{"parentUuid":"38dc8409-557c-4cec-9b44-a3a3c497fc05","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"50b9be8f-7c99-41a0-9aaa-5895bc15f702","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Rt4SfHmuBaw5LaamTAXhZE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Database connection - credentials loaded from environment variables:\n     2→# LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_URL, LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_USERNAME, LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_PASSWORD\n     3→\n     4→# Path to the master changelog file\n     5→changeLogFile=src/main/dbschema/master.xml\n     6→\n     7→# JDBC driver class to use\n     8→driver=org.postgresql.Driver\n     9→\n    10→# Classpath to the JDBC driver jar\n    11→classpath=etc/lib/postgresql-42.2.23.jar\n    12→\n    13→# Disable Liquibase Hub support\n    14→liquibase.hub.mode=off\n    15→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"uuid":"c947676b-658b-4a42-9016-5cb483bba22e","timestamp":"2026-04-27T21:15:16.408Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/opt/development/git/shokworks/intellxxdna/database/intell-lexxi-database/liquibase.properties","content":"# Database connection - credentials loaded from environment variables:\n# LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_URL, LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_USERNAME, LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_PASSWORD\n\n# Path to the master changelog file\nchangeLogFile=src/main/dbschema/master.xml\n\n# JDBC driver class to use\ndriver=org.postgresql.Driver\n\n# Classpath to the JDBC driver jar\nclasspath=etc/lib/postgresql-42.2.23.jar\n\n# Disable Liquibase Hub support\nliquibase.hub.mode=off\n","numLines":15,"startLine":1,"totalLines":15}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"38dc8409-557c-4cec-9b44-a3a3c497fc05","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/opt/development/g