{"parentUuid":"c947676b-658b-4a42-9016-5cb483bba22e","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HfkYnpNHxeAYiVjyLYeibw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix for this is to manually clean up the duplicate rows in the `DATABASECHANGELOGLOCK` table. You need to run these SQL commands against your database:\n\n```sql\n-- Delete all rows from the lock table\nDELETE FROM DATABASECHANGELOGLOCK;\n\n-- Re-insert the single correct row\nINSERT INTO DATABASECHANGELOGLOCK (ID, LOCKED) VALUES (1, FALSE);\n```\n\n**How to run it:**\n\nIf you have `psql` access, run:\n```bash\npsql $DATABASE_URL -c \"DELETE FROM DATABASECHANGELOGLOCK; INSERT INTO DATABASECHANGELOGLOCK (ID, LOCKED) VALUES (1, FALSE);\"\n```\n\nOr using Liquibase's built-in command (if it runs far enough):\n```bash\nliquibase releaseLocks\n```\n\n**What caused it:** The lock table ended up with 2 rows (IDs 1 and some duplicate), likely from a failed migration, a connection interruption, or running Liquibase against the DB from two different contexts simultaneously. Liquibase expects exactly 1 row with `ID=1`.\n\nAfter fixing, run Liquibase again — it should proceed normally."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":354,"cache_read_input_tokens":16784,"output_tokens":277,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":354,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaUy8jetWzmqLcRwjkDyP","type":"assistant","uuid":"36f91a07-cb65-4824-9c0d-8e6159d44947","timestamp":"2026-04-27T21:15:22.417Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/opt/development/git/shokworks/intellxxdna/database/intell-lexxi-database","sessionId":"850afccf-fa36-4fca-93c0-5845d130d4f1","version":"2.1.85","gitBranch":"main","slug":"reflective